Business Rules:
BR1: An airport must have a unique IATA code.
BR2: Each airport must belong to a city and country.
BR3: Airports cannot be deleted if they are linked to existing flights or tours.

System Requirements:
SYSREQ1: Implement a database constraint to ensure the uniqueness of the IATA code for each airport.
SYSREQ2: Establish foreign key relationships in the database to link airports with cities and countries.
SYSREQ3: Add validation in the service layer to prevent airport deletion if linked records exist in related tables.